<title type="html"><![CDATA[Quick question about PPUSTATUS/PPUADDR]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4574&amp;p=40045#p40045"><![CDATA[
Yes, it's safe to reset it just once.  If your NMI has the potential to be long enough, you may want to make sure it doesn't interrupt itself, but I doubt it's a problem.<br /><br />I've seen very few games, actually only one I can think of, that always read PPUSTATUS before setting the address.  Myself, I read it in every NMI.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Nov 14, 2008 1:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
